"```sql\nSELECT DISTINCT z.city, z.county\nFROM event e\nJOIN budget b ON e.event_id = b.link_to_event\nJOIN income i ON b.budget_id = i.link_to_budget\nJOIN member m ON i.link_to_member = m.member_id\nJOIN zip_code z ON m.zip = z.zip_code\nGROUP BY e.event_id, z.city, z.county\nHAVING COUNT(i.income_id) > 40;\n```\n\nThis SQL query selects the distinct city and county for events that have more than forty income records. It joins the necessary tables based on the foreign key relationships and groups the results by event ID, city, and county to apply the condition on the count of income records."